{"block": {"name": "admin", "text": "<p><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-blue\">UNIX CHALLENGE:<span class=\"wysiwyg-color-black\"> Basic Navigation: Creating a File</span></span></b></p><p>To warm up, we'll start with something simple: create a file called <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">message.txt</span>\u00a0in the working directory containing the text \"Hello, world!\" (no quotes)</p><p><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-red\">HINT:</span></b> You may want to use <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">vim</span>, a command line text editor, to write your code. Use the <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.openvim.com/\">Interactive </a><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.openvim.com/\">vim</a></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.openvim.com/\"> Tutorial</a> to learn how to use it if you are unfamiliar with it.<br></p>", "video": null, "animation": null, "options": {"time_limit": 3600}, "subtitle_files": [], "source": {"is_bootstrap": false, "image_id": 3, "memory": 64, "test_scenario": "def test_file_exists(s):\n    assert s.run('test -f /home/box/message.txt').succeeded, \"File 'message.txt' not found!\"\n\ndef test_file_content(s):\n    assert 'Hello, world!' == s.run('cat /home/box/message.txt').strip(), \"Incorrect file content\"", "bootstrap_script": "# This script provides the ability to configure a virtual machine in order\n# to prepare it for this challenge. It runs for every virtual machine created\n# prior to assigning it to a user. The execution time is limited to 5 minutes."}, "subtitles": {}, "tests_archive": null, "feedback_correct": "", "feedback_wrong": ""}, "id": "106052", "time": "2017-09-11T11:44:29.277491"}